/wiki/Zee_TV: Zee TV is an Indian pay television channel owned by Zee Entertainment Enterprises, a media and entertainment company based in Mumbai, Maharashtra. A part of the Essel Group, it started to broadcast on 2 October 1992 as the first Hindi-language subscription channel in India.
/wiki/Bairi_piya_(Serial): Bairi Piya is an Indian television drama that was broadcast on Colors TV each weekday starting from September 2009. It was produced by Ekta Kapoor and starred Sharad Kelkar (Thakur Digvijay Singh) and Supriya Kumari (Amoli). The show ended in September 2010.
/wiki/Sharad_Kelkar: Sharad Kelkar (born 7 October 1976) is an Indian actor, who appears in mainly Marathi films and Hindi films and also in television serials. He is also a former physical trainer. Sharad has performed in television series , Web Series, and Indian cinema including Bollywood, Marathi, Tollywood, Kolywood.
/wiki/Colors_(TV_channel): Viacom 18 Media Pvt. Limited is an Indian joint venture operation between ViacomCBS and TV18 based in Mumbai.  It was founded in November 2007 and owns various channels of ViacomCBS, as well as various consumer products in India.
/wiki/STAR_One: Star One was an Indian pay television network based in Mumbai. It was launched on 1 November 2004 and it was owned by Star TV and distributed worldwide by Fox International Channels. In November 2006, Star One was launched in the UK on Sky.
/wiki/Nachle_Ve_with_Saroj_Khan: Nachle Ve with Saroj Khan is Dance class show hosted by Saroj Khan. Nachle Ve with Saroj Khan Premiered from 21 January 2008.
/wiki/Imagine_TV: Imagine TV was a popular Hindi general entertainment channel, owned by Turner Broadcasting System (a subsidiary of Time Warner) based in New Delhi.
/wiki/Rakt_Sambandh: Rakt Sambandh is an Indian television series which aired on NDTV Imagine from 19 July 2010 to 1 April 2011.
/wiki/Pracheen_Chauhan: Pracheen Chauhan (born 7 July 1967) is an Indian television actor.
/wiki/Sony_Entertainment_Television_(Ind: Sony Entertainment Television (abbr. SET) is an Indian Hindi-language pay television channel that was launched in October 1996, and is owned by Sony Pictures Networks India, a subsidiary of the Japanese Sony.
/wiki/Looteri_Dulhan:
Looteri Dulhan was a fiction serial in Imagine TV. It is basically the story of orphan girl Billo.
Billo was played by Krishna Gokani who was later replaced by Supriya Kumari. The show concluded on 11 August 2011
/wiki/Mrunal_Jain: Mrunal Jain is an Indian Television and Bollywood film actor. He is best known for his role of Hiten, Sameer & Akash in popular show Bandini, Hitler Didi & Uttaran. He is currently seen in the Life OK finite series Nagarjuna- Ek Yoddha in 2016.
/wiki/Ratan_Ka_Rishta: Swayamvar Season 3, introduced as Ratan Ka Rishta on Imagine TV, is a marriage reality television show in India. It is the third season of Swayamvar. Bride of the season is Ratan Rajput. The show name is based on her name. It premiered on May 30, 2011 at 8.00 PM and airs Monday through Friday each week.
/wiki/Bhagonwali-Baante_Apni_Taqdeer: Bhagonwali is an Indian daily soap opera that aired on Zee TV. The series premiered on 6 December 2010. It is produced by Samidha Khalid's Creative Lab. It tells the story of Runjhun who brings good luck and fortune wherever she goes. However, her own life is riddled with misfortune and hard work because of her circumstances. This show went off air on 17 February 2012, ending with a total of 318 episodes.
/wiki/Himmanshoo_A._Malhotra: Himmanshu A. Malhotra (born Himanshu Malhotra) is an Indian actor. He participated and became the winner of Nach Baliye in 2015. He later participated in Fear Factor: Khatron Ke Khiladi in 2016.
/wiki/Anudamini: Anudamini is an Indian Hindi drama which premiered on DD National in 2014. It was produced by Raujesh Kumar Jain under the banner of Krish Movies. It starred Sachin Shroff, Ali Hassan and Supriya Kumari, Deepali Sahay, Neena Singh, Sham Malashkar and Raujesh Kumar Jain.
/wiki/Sachin_Shroff: Sachin Shroff (born 17 December 1972) is a businessman and TV personality. He is an actor, anchor and dancer.
/wiki/DD_National: DD National (formerly DD1) is a state-owned general entertainment television channel in India. It is the flagship channel of Doordarshan, India's public service broadcaster, and the most widely available terrestrial television channel in India.
/wiki/Diya_Aur_Baati_Hum: Diya Aur Baati Hum (transl. You are the lamp and I am the wick) is an Indian television soap opera that aired on Star Plus from 29 August 2011 to 10 September 2016 with a total of 1,487 episodes. It starred Anas Rashid and Deepika Singh.
/wiki/StarPlus: StarPlus is an Indian pay television channel owned by Star India. The network's programming consists of family dramas, comedies, youth-oriented reality shows, shows on crime and television films. It is also distributed internationally by The Walt Disney Company India, subsidiary of The Walt Disney Company.
/wiki/Kanan_Malhotra: Kanan Malhotra is an Indian model and television actor.
/wiki/Mere_Sai_-_Shraddha_Aur_Saburi: Mere Sai - Shraddha Aur Saburi (English: My Sai - Faith And Patience) is an Indian Hindi television series which premiered on Sony Entertainment Television on 25 September 2017. The show stars Tushar Dalvi in the lead role along with Kishori Godbole, Vaibhav Mangle in supporting roles.
/wiki/Supriya_Kumari: Supriya Kumari  is an Indian television actress who has played the lead in Balaji Telefilms serial Bairi Piya as Amoli on Colors (TV channel).
